    <refsection id="Description_MATBKSL">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            The MATBKSL block outputs the left matrix division. It is a solution to A*x=B. The higher input is the A matrix,
            the lower one is the B matrix, and the output is x.
            If A is an MxN1 matrix, B must be a MxN2 matrix where N1 and N2 can be different or equal. The output x
            is a N1xN2 matrix.
        </para>
        <para>
            The equivalent of MATBKSL is <link linkend="backslash">backslash (\)</link> Ã¯n Scilab.
        </para>
        <para/>
    </refsection>
